  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6591.43 sitting just above the 6589 GEX flip and below the massive 69.9B gamma wall at 6600, dealers are currently in position to sell any push toward 6600 while providing support on dips back to 6590. The PIN regime combined with the detected wall break and GEX surge suggests dealers are actively hedging as price tests these critical levels, creating a tight 6590-6600 range with heavy two-way flow. Key strikes to monitor are the 6600 max gamma wall above (major resistance) and 6590 support below, with any break of 6589 flip potentially triggering more aggressive dealer selling into weakness.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy trading trapped between 6590-6600 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
